&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade/Band - L&lt;br /&gt; Vacancy Hours  - 37.5 per week&lt;br /&gt; Contract Type - Fixed Term&lt;br /&gt; Contract End Date- 12 Months  &lt;br /&gt; Weekend Working - occasional &lt;br /&gt; Venue for Interview  - Virtual - Skype&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like the opportunity to positively influence the quality of the social care market, by supporting providers with a range of quality improvements during these unprecedented times? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If so, look no further.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Quality Improvement Team are looking for Quality Improvement Officers to join them at this challenging time, for a fixed term of 12 months to support the work of the Quality &amp; Market Improvement Team as part of the Directorate&#39;s Covid 19 response offer to the North Yorkshire Social Care market. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The Team work directly with care providers to support them to make a step change in the quality of service delivery, aimed at supporting a safe, quality and sustainable range of providers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The role is County wide, and as a Quality Improvement Officer, you will be responsible for ensuring that quality improvement activity is undertaken in line with legislative requirements and national Health &amp; Social Care best practice. You will have experience of managing or working at a senior level in a Registered Service and hold a Registered Manager or relevant professional qualification  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to provide leadership and direction will be key, proving leadership to staff teams and their managers, to ensure that services deliver on values, sense of purpose and the provision of high quality safe care; building capacity, identifying solutions and resolving issues along the way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; You would be joining us at a challenging and pivotal time for both North Yorkshire and the County Council&#39;s development as we take forward our devolution plans, and our work with partners to develop a distinctive public health and adult social care agenda.  This aims to support more people to live longer, healthier and independent lives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; You will develop and maintain effective working relationships with a range of stakeholders. Working with provider managers and senior managers from all types of Social Care provision, Learning Disability services, Residential and Nursing homes and Domiciliary care providers across North Yorkshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Supporting providers, working collaboratively with colleagues, providers and partners to collectively achieve satisfactory outcomes, drive quality improvement, and market sustainability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; In return, we can offer you a range of benefits including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;generous leave entitlement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;a local government pension scheme &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;training and development opportunities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible working&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whilst the post will currently have a homeworking office base, due to Covid - Office working restrictions, you will be required to work with providers in their locations across the county. We are supported with modern technology, which enables flexible working. Individual Covid 19 - Risk Assessments are in place. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; For an informal discussion about the role please contact Angie Austin Quality Improvement Team Manager – Tel: 01609 536986 or email at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;angie.austin@northyorks.gov.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Enhanced Level DBS Disclosure is required for appointment to this post. &lt;br /&gt; Priority will be given to NYCC staff under notice of redundancy or other authorised redeployees. If you wish to be considered for this vacancy through redeployment please contact the Recruitment Team.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; NYCC are committed to directly recruiting staff and will not accept applications nor services from agency suppliers in respect of our vacancies. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; We are committed to meeting the needs of our diverse community and aim to have a workforce reflecting this diversity. We are also committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of children, young people and adults. We expect all staff and volunteers to share this commitment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; North Yorkshire County Council (NYCC) advertise vacancies on behalf of schools and external organisations (third parties) in North Yorkshire. NYCC are not responsible for the recruitment/employment practices of third parties and accept no liability in relation to the vacancy and any subsequent recruitment/employment processes. Enquiries regarding the vacancy or practices should be made directly with the third party.&lt;/p&gt;
